  "body": "Vsphere volumes aren't relabelled in SELinux environment because they set `Managed: false` in volume attributes.\r\n\r\nThis flag is important for SELinux support to work - https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/kubelet_pods.go#L129\r\n\r\nCC @pmorie @childsb \r\n\r\nThe fix is obviously simple and I am happy to make it but I would like to know if there was any reason vsphere volumes don't follow example of other volume types that support SELinux? cc @kerneltime \r\n",
